        "title": "See also"
      },
      {
        "blocks": [
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "If you need a stricter way to identify a "
              },
              {
                "kind": "emphasis",
                "text": "numerical"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " scalar, use\n"
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "isinstance(x, numbers.Number)"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ", as that returns "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "False"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " for most\nnon-numerical elements such as strings."
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "inline": [
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": "In most cases "
              },
              {
                "external_url": "https://numpy.org/doc/stable/reference/generated/numpy.ndim(x) == 0.html",
                "href": "",
                "kind": "link",
                "target": "ndim(x) == 0",
                "text": "fnp.ndim(x) == 0"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " should be used instead of this function,\nas that will also return true for 0d arrays. This is how numpy overloads\nfunctions in the style of the "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "dx"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " arguments to "
              },
              {
                "external_url": "",
                "href": "/docs/api/ops/gradient",
                "kind": "link",
                "target": "gradient",
                "text": "gradient"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " and\nthe "
              },
              {
                "kind": "code",
                "text": "bins"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": " argument to "
              },
              {
                "external_url": "",
                "href": "/docs/api/ops/histogram",
                "kind": "link",
                "target": "histogram",
                "text": "histogram"
              },
              {
                "kind": "text",
                "text": ". Some key differences:"
              }
            ],
            "type": "paragraph"
          },
          {
            "raw_kind": "system_message",
            "raw_text": "<string>:11: (ERROR/3) Malformed table.\nRight border not aligned or missing.\n\n+------------------------------------+---------------+-------------------+\n| x                                  |``isscalar(x)``|``fnp.ndim(x) == 0``|\n+====================================+===============+===================+\n| PEP 3141 numeric objects           | ``True``      | ``True``          |\n| (including builtins)               |               |                   |\n+------------------------------------+---------------+-------------------+\n| builtin string and buffer objects  | ``True``      | ``True``          |\n+------------------------------------+---------------+-------------------+\n| other builtin objects, like        | ``False``     | ``True``          |\n| `pathlib.Path`, `Exception`,       |               |                   |\n| the result of `re.compile`         |               |                   |\n+------------------------------------+---------------+-------------------+\n| third-party objects like           | ``False``     | ``True``          |\n| `matplotlib.figure.Figure`         |               |                   |\n+------------------------------------+---------------+-------------------+\n| zero-dimensional numpy arrays      | ``False``     | ``True``          |\n+------------------------------------+---------------+-------------------+\n| other numpy arrays                 | ``False``     | ``False``         |\n+------------------------------------+---------------+-------------------+\n| `list`, `tuple`, and other         | ``False``     | ``False``         |\n| sequence objects                   |               |                   |\n+------------------------------------+---------------+-------------------+",
            "type": "raw_block"
          }
        ],
        "title": "Notes"
      },
